The paper discusses the data-processing inequality and its extensions in information theory, which is a subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on channels and Bayesian networks, which are topics related to information theory, machine learning, and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses concepts related to machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM).
